---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for Color Helper — learn how your data is handled when using our color tools."
  canonical="https://color-helper.com/privacy/"
>
  <div class="content-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-wrapper">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

        <h2>Data Collection</h2>
        <p>
          Color Helper does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data. All tools run entirely in your
          browser using client-side JavaScript. No account creation is required and no session data is tracked.
        </p>

        <h2>Image Processing</h2>
        <p>
          When you use the Image Color Picker, your image is processed locally on your device using the HTML5
          Canvas API. No image data is uploaded to any server. The entire process happens within your browser.
        </p>

        <h2>Local Storage</h2>
        <p>
          The Color Picker tool uses localStorage to save your custom color palette. This data never leaves your
          browser and can be cleared at any time through your browser settings.
        </p>

        <h2>Analytics</h2>
        <p>
          This MVP does not include any analytics or tracking scripts. We do not use cookies, fingerprinting, or
          any other tracking mechanisms.
        </p>

        <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          We use Google Fonts for typography. Google may collect usage data such as your IP address when loading
          fonts. Please refer to Google's privacy policy for more information.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page. We encourage you
          to review this policy periodically.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this privacy policy, please reach out to us at
          hello@color-helper.com.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .content-page {
    padding: 2rem 0;
  }
  .content-wrapper {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }
  h2 {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }
  p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }
</style>
